---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Aditya Nannapaneni"
  description="About Aditya Nannapaneni, Senior Applied Scientist at AWS working on production AI systems and evaluation."
>
  <section class="section-space">
    <div class="container-site max-w-[760px]">
      <SectionHeading title="About" eyebrow="Seattle, WA" />

      <div class="mb-10 overflow-hidden border border-border bg-white sm:max-w-sm">
        <img
          src="/images/aditya_potrait.png"
          alt="Portrait of Aditya Nannapaneni"
          width="927"
          height="854"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          class="h-auto w-full object-cover"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="prose-site space-y-5">
        <p>
          I’m a Senior Applied Scientist at AWS. My technical focus is production
          AI systems: LLM serving and evaluation, agent reliability, retrieval,
          recommendation, and the shared infrastructure that lets research ideas
          become durable products.
        </p>
        <p>
          My working style sits between applied research and engineering
          delivery. I care about model quality, but also about measurement,
          latency, cost, failure modes, and whether teams can adopt the system
          without heroic effort. Recent research covers RAG attribution metrics
          and persistent memory and governance for always-on agents.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside AWS, I’m interested in building intelligent products at the
          intersection of AI, health, and sports—including PharmaSage and
          CourtMates. Entrepreneurship for me is another way to pressure-test
          whether an idea survives contact with real users.
        </p>
        <p>
          I’m based in Seattle and compete in tennis. Training and match play
          shape how I think about performance: measure carefully, iterate under
          constraints, and stay calm when the scoreboard moves.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
